    {
      "id": "primitive-view-consumption-schema-examples",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "9. Examples",
      "position": {
        "x": -984.3601010653929,
        "y": 737.8333333333335
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Examples\n\n**Valid:**\n- `port` consumes `port-view` by default\n- `bridge` uses bridge-native rendering and falls back to `icon-view` for compact target identity\n- ordinary node presence consumes `node-view`\n- readable artifact surfaces consume `document-view`\n- editor surfaces consume `editor-view`\n\n**Invalid (must fail or degrade visibly):**\n- a port consuming arbitrary `ui-view` just because it exists\n- a bridge rendering a document card as if it were public content\n- an editor surface silently consuming `port-view`\n- primitive/view pairing inferred from stale node ids instead of role law",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
